      "body" : "> 2020-06-22T10:39:38Z FlushStateToDisk: write coins cache to disk (47561940 coins, 6570934kB) completed (3272.20s)\r\n\r\n6.5GB in an hour means you're pushing 1.4MB/s to your storage. Syncing a very IO heavy database to a slow (USB2? FireWire?) storage device is just never going to be performant. It's not \"hanging\" so much as the entire node is halted for an hour (including the networking thread) waiting for data to desperately be written to disk. ",
